Title: Call of Duty Black Ops 4 Multiplayer Reveal Trailer
Comment:
When the first Black Ops came out, I wasn‚Äôt too blown away. The game was fun, but that‚Äôs what you‚Äôd expect from a CoD game. It wasn‚Äôt till Black Ops II where I was really impressed. It had a great branching narrative with interesting new and returning characters that made every moment of the campaign rewarding. 

The multiplayer was amazing as well, though BOII was never my favorite game (none of the CoD games were in that manner), some of my favorite gaming memories was due to the addictive multiplayer and the surprisingly supportive community playing it. 

But now we‚Äôre here. Black Ops III was horrible and now it seems Black Ops IIII will continue to disappoint. There use to be value in there game, they use to push the boundaries of what could be done and they always blew it out of the water... but they‚Äôve stopped trying to make quality games and instead try to make a quick buck trying to squeeze every penny out of us even after our initial purchase of the game.

I always knew there‚Äôd come a time where CoD would lose itself, but now that it‚Äôs here, I can‚Äôt help but feel sad. I still have hope for the franchise, but every time they come out with a weak entry carrying that legendary Call of Duty name, that hope dies a little. Hope they get the hint someday, but until they do, I‚Äôll  just have to keep playing the old greats. Back when they cared for players.
